  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6758.86 sitting right in the thick negative gamma zone between 6750-6765 strikes, dealers are actively buying this dip as part of their short gamma hedging, creating tactical support but amplifying any directional moves. The breakout regime with -200B total GEX means dealers will continue this momentum-amplifying behavior - buying rallies toward the 6800 positive gamma wall where they'll flip to selling, and aggressively buying any further dips below current levels. Watch for violent whipsaws around these 6750-6765 negative gamma walls, with 6800 acting as the key resistance level where dealer flow reverses.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect amplified volatile swings with dealer buying supporting dips but strong resistance near 6800.",
